  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-03 16:43 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC still contested, SOL max bearish again\n\n**Task:** Re-check P1 copy intelligence after BTC modestly rebuilt but remained below clean confirmation, focusing on whether BTC can reclaim >$16M/$17M or whether alt bearish pressure intensifies.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 7L/1S**, **ETH 2L/6S**, **SOL 0L/8S**.\n- Current top-book notional: **BTC +$15.57M net long**, **ETH -$36.70M net short**, **SOL -$10.94M net short**, **HYPE -$10.63M net short**.\n- BTC slipped from **+$15.85M** to **+$15.57M**; still above `$15M`, but not rebuilding toward `$17M`.\n- BTC breadth improved from **6L/2S** to **7L/1S**, but the only short is small: `beatmaker1@proton.me` BTC SHORT **$80K**.\n- BTC long anchors: `anon-0xfc66` **$5.63M** unchanged, `anon-0xecb6` **$4.45M** down from **$4.62M**, `anon-0x8fcc` **$4.30M** unchanged and still below **$5M** clean-anchor size, `anon-0x57dd` **$1.12M** stable.\n- ETH remains high-conviction bearish: **2L/6S**, net **-$36.70M**, with `anon-0x3bca` ETH SHORT still material at **$1.82M**.\n- SOL returned to max bearish breadth: **0L/8S**, net **-$10.94M**.\n- HYPE bearish pressure intensified by count: **2L/7S**, net **-$10.63M**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-still-contested-sol-max-bearish-again-2026-05-03-1643.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC is still contested and has not rebuilt cleanly. Breadth looks better, but notional is leaking and the key anchor `8fcc` is stuck below the `$5M` threshold. Meanwhile SOL is back to a max-bearish 0L/8S book, validating the P3 warning that SOL long micro-drift rows need conflict tagging.\n\n**Decision:** Keep BTC label **bullish but contested / distribution watch**. Do not upgrade until BTC net reclaims **>$17M** and `8fcc` rebuilds near/above **$5M**. Distribution downgrade triggers if BTC net falls below **$15M**. Hard downgrade remains BTC net below **$10M** or `anon-0x8fcc` flips short above **$2M**. Keep ETH bearish confidence high. Upgrade SOL back to **max bearish leaderboard conviction**. Keep HYPE bearish confidence high by count/notional. No PM Sunday exception. No HL live trade while notional guard blocks execution.\n\n**Next:** Watch BTC `$15M` vs `$17M` boundaries and whether `ecb6` keeps trimming. Also keep SOL conflict gating high priority for P3, because SOL returned to 0L/8S while the recent SOL micro-drift long lost.\n\n## 2026-05-03 16:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] RANGE/NEUTRAL low vol, BTC rebuilds modestly\n\n**Task:** Refresh P4 alpha after P3 showed strict RANGE micro-drift stable and base STRONG_TREND rows improving, checking whether P4 remains range-friendly or shifts toward trend risk.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P4**.\n- Fresh alpha snapshot: `2026-05-03T16:37:43.498218+00:00`.\n- Classifier remain",
